    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect hex character conversion in utility function\n\n### Summary\nThe `hex_char_to_hex_value` function in common utilities was not properly converting some hexadecimal characters, causing incorrect values to be returned when parsing hex strings. This affected modules that rely on hex string parsing for configuration.\n\nThis fix rewrites the character conversion logic to use explicit range checks instead of bit manipulation.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/utils.c`: Rewrote `hex_char_to_hex_value` with clearer conditional logic\n- `common/utils/utils.h`: No changes to function signature, maintains API compatibility\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen parsing hexadecimal strings containing lowercase letters, some characters were being converted to incorrect values. Users reported configuration failures when specifying MAC addresses or other hex values in lower case format.\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by calling `hex_char_to_hex_value('a')` through `hex_string_to_hex_value()` with a string like \"a1b2c3\" - the resulting byte values would be incorrect.\n\n"
}